{"ts":"2026-06-26T00:14:36.539Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Initial Results**\n\nI've examined the initial results and noticed some interesting patterns. The \"SES\" hits seem to be false positives, largely stemming from matches on common words containing \"ses\" like \"session\" or \"clauses,\" and not actual AWS SES usage. Similarly, \"S3\" is showing up due to static text descriptions and not direct S3 implementation, such as static descriptions like \"compliance: Real-time auditing across database schemas and S3\". This points to the need for refined keyword filtering.\n\n\n**Refining Contact Form Analysis**\n\nI've shifted focus to the contact form's implementation. My analysis of `handleContactSubmit` in `components/ContactSection.tsx` reveals an API call to `/api/contact`. I've decided to replace the backend interaction with a frontend mock, simulating network latency with a 1000ms `setTimeout`. This will allow local testing without backend dependencies. The placeholder copy should say \"FastAPI /\".\n\n\n**Verifying Backend Integration**\n\nI'm now focusing on ensuring the frontend mock clearly indicates future backend integration. I'll modify the placeholder copy, making sure it explicitly states that FastAPI integration will be added in a later release. To maintain clarity, I'm examining the code around `handleContactSubmit` in `components/ContactSection.tsx`, specifically lines 59-111, to identify the best place for this modification. My goal is to add a clear message about future backend integration to avoid user confusion.\n\n\n**Evaluating Error Handling**\n\nI'm now focusing on improving the error-handling within the contact form submission. I've examined the `handleContactSubmit` function to refine how we present messages to users. Specifically, I'm analyzing the catch block and the `response.json()` error parsing to improve user feedback during backend errors. I intend to enhance the error messages in `setNotification` calls to provide more actionable guidance.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T00:14:36.543Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"gntrgles","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/ContactSection.tsx","old_text":"  const handleContactSubmit = async (event: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => {\n    event.preventDefault();\n\n    try {\n      setIsSubmitting(true);\n      const response = await fetch(\"/api/contact\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: {\n          \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n        },\n        body: JSON.stringify(contactForm),\n      });\n\n      if (response.ok) {\n        setContactForm({\n          fullName: \"\",\n          fullNameDetail: \"\",\n          company: \"\",\n          companyDetail: \"\",\n          businessEmail: \"\",\n          businessEmailDetail: \"\",\n        });\n        setNotification({\n          open: true,\n          type: \"success\",\n          title: \"Message sent successfully\",\n          message:\n            \"Thanks for reaching out. Your details have been delivered to our team, and we’ll review them shortly.\",\n        });\n      } else {\n        const error = await response.json().catch(() => null);\n        setNotification({\n          open: true,\n          type: \"error\",\n          title: \"Message could not be sent\",\n          message:\n            error?.message ??\n            \"Please try again in a moment or check the form details and resubmit.\",\n        });\n      }\n    } catch {\n      setNotification({\n        open: true,\n        type: \"error\",\n        title: \"Something went wrong\",\n        message:\n          \"Please try again in a moment. If the issue continues, reach out to us directly.\",\n      });\n    } finally {\n      setIsSubmitting(false);\n    }\n  };","new_text":"  const handleContactSubmit = async (event: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => {\n    event.preventDefault();\n\n    try {\n      set